        "\n",
        "Padding is done using the specified fill character (default is a space).\n",

        "# count(x: str, __start: SupportsIndex | None = ..., __end: SupportsIndex | None = ...) -> int\n",
        "S.count(sub[, start[, end]]) -> int\n",
        "\n",
        "Return the number of non-overlapping occurrences of substring sub in\n",
        "string S[start:end].  \n",
        "\n",
        "Optional arguments start and end are\n",
        "interpreted as in slice notation."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "lP_k_gCNiv_l"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "var_str = \"Peppa pig personal likes Python Programming\"\n",
        "print(var_str.count('p'))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('a'))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('e'))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('P'))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('p',0,5))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('p',0,11))\n",

        "print(var_str.count('p',11,len(var_str)))\n",
        "print(var_str.count('a',20,len(var_str)))\n",

        "# endswith(__suffix: str | Tuple[str, ...], __start: SupportsIndex | None = ..., __end: SupportsIndex | None = ...) -> bool\n",

        "\n",
        "Return True if S ends with the specified suffix, False otherwise.\n",
        "With optional start, test S beginning at that position.\n",
        "With optional end, stop comparing S at that position.\n",
        "suffix can also be a tuple of strings to try."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "x_U_rN6m4XnG"
      }

        "# index(__sub: str, __start: SupportsIndex | None = ..., __end: SupportsIndex | None = ...) -> int\n",

        "\n",
        "Return the lowest index in S where substring sub is found, \n",

        "# translate(__table: Mapping[int, int | str | None] | Sequence[int | str | None]) -> str\n",

        "Unicode ordinals, strings, or None.\n",

        "dictionary or list.  If this operation raises LookupError, the character is\n",
        "left untouched.  Characters mapped to None are deleted."

      "source": [
        "# translate(__table: Mapping[int, int | str | None] | Sequence[int | str | None]) -> str\n",
        "Replace each character in the string using the given translation table.\n",
        "\n",
        "  table\n",
        "    Translation table, which must be a mapping of Unicode ordinals to\n",
        "Unicode ordinals, strings, or None.\n",
        "\n",
        "The table must implement lookup/indexing via __getitem__, for instance a\n",
        "dictionary or list.  If this operation raises LookupError, the character is\n",
        "left untouched.  Characters mapped to None are deleted."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "KFZJ0seklxVq"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "mydict = {83:  80}\n",
        "var_str = \"Hello Sarika!\"\n",
        "print(var_str.translate(mydict))"
